Reasoning: The paper discusses the fundamental principles of computing and the interaction between the abstract computational level and the physical device level. It also covers a range of non-standard computing scenarios and defines the critical notion of a 'computational entity'. Based on these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
